    "description": "The test setup consists of an electric induction motor driving a centrifugal pump, instrumented for vibration and motor-current monitoring. Standard deep-groove ball bearings are installed in both the motor and pump. Various bearing faults and mechanical defects are intentionally introduced (e.g., inner-race, outer-race, rolling-element damage, lubrication contamination). Sensor data are recorded under controlled operating conditions to create a labeled dataset for condition monitoring and fault diagnosis.",
